name: 威尔·因曼
introduction: William Dominguez Inman is a Mexican-American actor with training from The Second City, The Theatre School at DePaul University, and Columbia University in the City of New York.His stage experience includes productions of INTO THE WOODS, THE MUSIC MAN, and ALMOST, MAINE. On-screen, he has credits in TRANSFORMERS: AGE OF EXTINCTION directed by Michael Bay and Dick Wolf's CHICAGO FIRE.Up next, he can be seen in THE YELLOW DIARY written and directed by Patricia Fritze, THE FOOLS from filmmaker Andrea Studinger, and Vuk Lungulov-Klotz's MUTT which premiered at the Sundance Film Festival 2023 in the U.S. Dramatic Competition.
